1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:01,100
hello

2
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:07,300
today we are going to see how to automate thuamcraft 4 infusion using Steve's factory manager

3
00:00:07,766 --> 00:00:11,566
so, once we built an infusion altar stable enough

4
00:00:11,566 --> 00:00:13,766
we can start with the automation

5
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:18,233
by the way try to get the stability as high as you can

6
00:00:18,233 --> 00:00:22,300
since the automation benefits a lot from extra stability

7
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:24,666
anyways, to get started

8
00:00:24,666 --> 00:00:31,600
we want an accessible interface to drop the crafted items and a chest where the interface will drop ingredients

9
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:34,000
once everything is prepared

10
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,066
we can drop the machine inventory manager and connect it to everything

11
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:43,166
it is enough for the cables to touch all of the wanted inventories from any side

12
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:45,633
the altar doesn't care about the symmetry

13
00:00:46,166 --> 00:00:51,500
we can check that the cable connected to everything by creating an output on the SFM controller

14
00:00:52,066 --> 00:00:55,866
however managing the pedestals like that is going to be annoying

15
00:00:55,866 --> 00:01:00,300
so we can use a labeler to rename the blocks we will be interacting with

16
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:04,200
the first and most important is the pedestal in the middle

17
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:06,066
which we'll show name accordingly

18
00:01:07,066 --> 00:01:11,033
and we can see that we can now easily identify in our controller

19
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:15,266
but to keep the items balanced on the pedestals

20
00:01:15,266 --> 00:01:17,066
we want to rename all of them

21
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:19,433
and to make things easier

22
00:01:19,433 --> 00:01:22,500
we rename them in the order we want them to be filled

23
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,433
here is an example

24
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:29,033
but just go in the order you would normally fill the pedestals while doing infusion

25
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:32,666
and now time to start our program

26
00:01:32,866 --> 00:01:34,666
we could use some better trigger

27
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:37,200
but we are going with the default timed one

28
00:01:37,366 --> 00:01:39,366
we can set the timing as we want

29
00:01:39,366 --> 00:01:42,566
more frequent causes more lag but works faster

30
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:46,366
next we have to move the items on the pedestals

31
00:01:46,566 --> 00:01:48,433
to make things clean and nice

32
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:50,400
we can use a command group

33
00:01:51,666 --> 00:01:53,700
this is basically a subprogram

34
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:57,900
that will make a lot of instruction take only a single block of space

35
00:01:58,666 --> 00:02:01,233
to interact with the flow of the upper program

36
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:04,833
we can use group nodes inputs and outputs

37
00:02:05,966 --> 00:02:09,066
now that we have our nice group for filling the pedestals

38
00:02:09,066 --> 00:02:11,833
we have to actually do the item insertion

39
00:02:14,266 --> 00:02:16,300
we start by creating an input

40
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:19,300
which will take items as input from the chest

41
00:02:20,066 --> 00:02:23,700
then one by one we add all of the outputs

42
00:02:23,866 --> 00:02:27,300
we go in sequential order to fill all of the pedestals

43
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,233
starting from the middle one

44
00:02:30,766 --> 00:02:32,666
and to make that work

45
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:36,600
we must make patterns with the middle item as first in the pattern

46
00:02:37,766 --> 00:02:41,700
and we fill the subgroup with all the outputs in sequential order

47
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,800
with that done we can go back to the actual program

48
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:48,633
and before doing anything else

49
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:49,833
we will want a condition

50
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:53,700
that will check if there are any items already present on the altar

51
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:57,600
we are going to do this check before anything else

52
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:01,033
to make it work we select all of the pedestals

53
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:03,366
to make it match any possible item

54
00:03:03,366 --> 00:03:06,600
we select one random item but in match all mode

55
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:08,900
right click to open the menu

56
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:12,366
now, if there are no items on the altar

57
00:03:12,366 --> 00:03:15,066
we can proceed with inserting a new crafting

58
00:03:15,666 --> 00:03:18,500
and to ensure that so far everything works

59
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:21,200
we can already try to craft something

60
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:22,800
as you can see

61
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,400
the items are already placed with the main in the middle

62
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,600
and the others in a balanced pattern

63
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:30,233
to automatically start the infusion

64
00:03:30,233 --> 00:03:31,666
we need an infusion claw

65
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:34,433
equipped with a wand that has some vis inside

66
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:36,466
and to make it work

67
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:39,766
it needs a Redstone signal to start the infusion

68
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:43,566
so we add a Redstone emitter which we properly rename

69
00:03:43,966 --> 00:03:47,566
to control it we add a Redstone emitter to our program

70
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,166
we select the emitter

71
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:51,766
and set it to output a strong signal

72
00:03:51,866 --> 00:03:55,466
and that shall be done after the items are placed on the pedestals

73
00:03:56,066 --> 00:03:57,900
then we add a second emitter

74
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:00,400
with strength to 0 to shut it off

75
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:06,800
for the moment we shall turn it off once the pedestals have been filled and infusion already started

76
00:04:07,366 --> 00:04:10,566
and to avoid having the Redstone emitter always on

77
00:04:10,566 --> 00:04:14,800
we add a condition that will start the process only if there are items ready

78
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:18,033
otherwise it shut off the starting signal

79
00:04:19,366 --> 00:04:22,233
and now it is time to test if this works

80
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:25,500
the starting Redstone signal barely made into the video

81
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:28,466
since it went off as soon as I closed the terminal

82
00:04:28,466 --> 00:04:30,366
but the process is starting

83
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,800
after the long animation of the claw

84
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,633
the long animation of the infusion starts

85
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:39,866
and after all of the essential and items are collected

86
00:04:39,866 --> 00:04:41,166

we get our item


87
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:45,433
now we only have to add a couple of instructions to retrieve those

88
00:04:45,766 --> 00:04:48,266
but before retrieving any item

89
00:04:48,266 --> 00:04:51,166
we must be sure the infusion is completed

90
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:53,233
to do so we make a condition

91
00:04:53,233 --> 00:04:56,900
that will check for items in any of the pedestal but the mid one

92
00:04:57,433 --> 00:05:00,400
we shall make that check after the more generic one

93
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:05,033
and if it is false or better there are no secondary items

94
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:08,400
then we can pull out the crafted item on the mid pedestal

95
00:05:08,866 --> 00:05:11,266
so we take as input the mid pedestal

96
00:05:11,266 --> 00:05:15,833
and we output to the interface to complete the crafting that AE2 is waiting

97
00:05:16,266 --> 00:05:18,266
and now we can do a test run

98
00:05:18,266 --> 00:05:20,966
where we can see that everything works fine

99
00:05:21,066 --> 00:05:24,200
or maybe the items was extracted too quickly

100
00:05:24,766 --> 00:05:29,900
the main issue now is that this speed is hardly acceptable for an automated setup

101
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:34,566
so we add a couple of world accelerator in tile entity mode

102
00:05:35,066 --> 00:05:37,966
those will use 12 amps of the used tier

103
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,033
which might be a lot for some people

104
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,800
so we can add a machine controller cover

105
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,100
to toggle those on only when needed

106
00:05:45,566 --> 00:05:48,300
we turn them on when the infusion is started

107
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:52,366
and then we turn those off when the items are retrieved from the infusion

108
00:05:52,466 --> 00:05:54,900
and here we also turn off the claw

109
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:58,800
since we must ensure it toggles on and off to properly work

110
00:05:59,166 --> 00:06:02,066
and now time to see if this is fast enough

111
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:04,266
and I'd say it's good enough

112
00:06:04,966 --> 00:06:07,366
finally we make a more sustained test

113
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:09,500
to check if everything works fine

114
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,900
and after a little bit of debugging

115
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:13,466
it works well enough

116
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:19,166
the only thing left to do is to make sure we do not lack of essence when we autocraft

117
00:06:19,266 --> 00:06:22,200
we can do that by using an advanced provider

118
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,866
but I never fiddled with it

119
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:27,533
or, a different approach is to set a slightly higher timer delay

120
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:31,233
and extract the middle item regardless of the how the process is doing

121
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:33,566
to stop anything that could have gone wrong

122
00:06:33,966 --> 00:06:38,100

also you can have an input redstone signal to inhibit the automation


123
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:44,366
and turn on the world accelerator for some rare occasion where you will want to do manual infusions

124
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:01,100
大家好

125
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:07,300
今天我们将看到如何使用SFM自动神秘4注魔

126
00:00:07,766 --> 00:00:11,566

那么，一旦我们建了一个足够稳定的注魔祭坛


127
00:00:11,566 --> 00:00:13,766
我们可以开始自动化了

128
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:18,233
顺便说一句，要让稳定性尽可能高

129
00:00:18,233 --> 00:00:22,300
因为自动化从额外的稳定性中受益匪浅

130
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:24,666
不管怎样，开始吧

131
00:00:24,666 --> 00:00:31,600
我们想要一个输出原料的ME接口
和一个可以输入原料的箱子

132
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:34,000
一旦一切准备就绪

133
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,066
我们放下工厂管理器
并将其连接到所有东西上

134
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:43,166
线缆能接触到要连接的方块的任何一面就行

135
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:45,633
祭坛不在乎对称性

136
00:00:46,166 --> 00:00:51,500
我们可以通过在SFM控制器上创建输出
来检查线缆是否连接到所有东西

137
00:00:52,066 --> 00:00:55,866
然而，这样管理基座会很烦人

138
00:00:55,866 --> 00:01:00,300

我们可以使用贴标器来重命名要交互的方块


139
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:04,200
第一个也是最重要的是中间的基座

140
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:06,066
我们打上相应的名称

141
00:01:07,066 --> 00:01:11,033

现在就可以很容易地在管理器中认出它


142
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:15,266
但是为了保持基座上物品的平衡

143
00:01:15,266 --> 00:01:17,066

我们要把所有这些重命名了


144
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:19,433

为了让事情更轻松


145
00:01:19,433 --> 00:01:22,500
我们按照"希望填充它们的顺序"重命名它们

146
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,433

比如下面这个例子


147
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:29,033

只要按照你一般注魔时填充基座的顺序就可以


148
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:32,666
现在是时候开始写我们的程序了

149
00:01:32,866 --> 00:01:34,666
我们可以用更好的触发器

150
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:37,200
但我们要使用默认计时的

151
00:01:37,366 --> 00:01:39,366
我们可以随心所欲地设定时间

152
00:01:39,366 --> 00:01:42,566
更频繁会导致更多卡顿，但工作速度更快

153
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:46,366
接下来我们必须移动基座上的物品

154
00:01:46,566 --> 00:01:48,433

为了让面板看起来更清爽


155
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:50,400
我们可以使用命令组

156
00:01:51,666 --> 00:01:53,700
这基本上是一个子程序

157
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:57,900
这将使大量指令只占用一块空间

158
00:01:58,666 --> 00:02:01,233
要与上层程序的流程交互

159
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:04,833
我们可以使用输入和输出的组节点

160
00:02:05,966 --> 00:02:09,066
现在我们有了一个很好的、用来填充基座的命令组

161
00:02:09,066 --> 00:02:11,833
我们必须真正地写出插入物品的命令

162
00:02:14,266 --> 00:02:16,300
我们首先创建一个输入模块

163
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:19,300
它将箱子里的物品作为输入

164
00:02:20,066 --> 00:02:23,700
然后我们一个接一个地添加所有输出

165
00:02:23,866 --> 00:02:27,300
我们按顺序填满所有的基座

166
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,233
从中间开始

167
00:02:30,766 --> 00:02:32,666
为了让它发挥作用

168
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:36,600
我们的样板必须要把祭坛中间的物品第一个输出

169
00:02:37,766 --> 00:02:41,700
我们按顺序把命令组里的所有的输出写好

170
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,800
完成后，我们可以回到主程序

171
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:48,633
在做其他任何事情之前

172
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:49,833

我们需要一个条件模块


173
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:53,700

来检查祭坛上是否已经有任意物品


174
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:57,600

这个检查必须要放在做其他操作之前


175
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:01,033
为此，我们选择了所有的基座

176
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:03,366
使其匹配任何可能的物品

177
00:03:03,366 --> 00:03:06,600
我们随便选一个物品，打开"匹配所有"模式

178
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:08,900
右键打开菜单来进行这项设置

179
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:12,366

那么，如果祭坛上没有东西


180
00:03:12,366 --> 00:03:15,066
我们可以做新的一批合成

181
00:03:15,666 --> 00:03:18,500
要确保到目前为止一切正常

182
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:21,200
我们已经可以尝试制作一些东西

183
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:22,800
如你所见

184
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,400
主要的物品已经放在中间了

185
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,600

其他的物品呈现对称的样式放置


186
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:30,233
要自动开始注魔

187
00:03:30,233 --> 00:03:31,666
我们需要一个注魔爪

188
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:34,433
里面有一根有vis的魔杖

189
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:36,466
要让注魔爪工作

190
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:39,766
它需要红石信号开始注魔

191
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:43,566

所以我们添加了一个红石发射器，打上了一个合适的名字


192
00:03:43,966 --> 00:03:47,566
为了控制它，我们在程序中添加了一个红石发射器模块

193
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,166
我们选择发射器

194
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:51,766
并将其设置为输出强信号

195
00:03:51,866 --> 00:03:55,466

输出指令会在物品放到基座上后进行


196
00:03:56,066 --> 00:03:57,900
然后我们添加第二个发射器模块

197
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:00,400
强度设置为0以关闭它

198
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:06,800
目前，一旦填充过基座并且开始了注魔，我们将关闭注魔爪

199
00:04:07,366 --> 00:04:10,566
并避免红石发射器始终打开

200
00:04:10,566 --> 00:04:14,800
我们添加了一个条件，仅当有物品准备好时才会启动该过程

201
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:18,033
否则它会关闭启动信号

202
00:04:19,366 --> 00:04:22,233
现在是时候测试这是否有效了

203
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:25,500
开始注魔的红石信号几乎没有进入视频

204
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:28,466
因为我一关闭终端它的强度就被设置成0了

205
00:04:28,466 --> 00:04:30,366
但这个过程正在开始

206
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,800
在注魔爪的漫长动画之后

207
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,633
注魔的漫长动画开始了

208
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:39,866
在收集到所有的源质和物品后

209
00:04:39,866 --> 00:04:41,166
我们得到了注魔输出

210
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:45,433

现在我们只需要加几个指令来取出产品


211
00:04:45,766 --> 00:04:48,266
但在取回任何物品之前

212
00:04:48,266 --> 00:04:51,166
我们必须确保注魔完成

213
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:53,233
为此，我们用一个条件模块

214
00:04:53,233 --> 00:04:56,900
检查除中间基座外的任何基座是否含有物品

215
00:04:57,433 --> 00:05:00,400
我们将在检查所有基座之后再进行该检查

216
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:05,033
如果输出是假，就说明没有次要物品

217
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:08,400
然后我们可以把中间底座上合成好的东西拿出来

218
00:05:08,866 --> 00:05:11,266
所以我们把中间基座作为输入

219
00:05:11,266 --> 00:05:15,833
输出到ME接口，以完成AE正在等待的合成

220
00:05:16,266 --> 00:05:18,266
现在我们可以试运行了

221
00:05:18,266 --> 00:05:20,966
一切正常

222
00:05:21,066 --> 00:05:24,200
或许物品提取得太快了

223
00:05:24,766 --> 00:05:29,900
现在的主要问题是，这速度对于自动化来说难以接受

224
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:34,566
所以我们添加了几个方块实体模式的世界加速器

225
00:05:35,066 --> 00:05:37,966
这些将使用12 A的机器所在电压的电

226
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,033
这对某些人来说可能很多

227
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,800
所以我们可以添加一个机器控制覆盖板

228
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,100
仅在需要时打开加速器

229
00:05:45,566 --> 00:05:48,300
我们在开始注魔时打开它们

230
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:52,366
然后在取出注魔好的物品时关闭它们

231
00:05:52,466 --> 00:05:54,900
我们此时也关闭注魔爪

232
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:58,800
因为我们必须确保它打开和关闭以正常工作

233
00:05:59,166 --> 00:06:02,066
现在是时候看看这是否足够快了

234
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:04,266

这样就差不多了


235
00:06:04,966 --> 00:06:07,366
最后我们做一个更持久的测试

236
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:09,500
检查是否一切正常

237
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,900
经过一点调试

238
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:13,466
它工作得很好

239
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:19,166
唯一要做的就是确保合成时不缺乏源质

240
00:06:19,266 --> 00:06:22,200
我们可以通过使用高级注魔供应器来做到这一点

241
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,866

但我从没研究过这东西


242
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:27,533
或者，另一种方法是设置稍高的定时器延迟

243
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:31,233
不管流程进行到哪，强制取出中间基座的物品

244
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:33,566
阻止任何可能出错的事情

245
00:06:33,966 --> 00:06:38,100
你还可以输入红石信号来暂停自动化

246
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:44,366
并在需要进行手动注魔的罕见场合打开世界加速器

247
00:02:20,066 --> 00:02:29,233
（这一步可以通过变量模块来简化，创建一个包含所有基座的变量，这样就只需要在一个输入模块里选择这个变量作为输出）

248
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:08,400
（任何一个基座有物品为真，除中间基座外的任何基座有物品为假，推断出只有中间基座有物品）

